<HEADLINE>
FT  21 OCT 94 / International Company News: Solid advances at GM divisions
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Revenues at EDS, the computer services subsidiary of General Motors, climbed
23 per cent in its third quarter from a year ago, to Dollars 2.56bn, writes
Richard Waters.
Mr Les Alberthal, chairman and chief executive, attributed the advance in
sales to strong growth in Europe and Asia. The growth supported a 13 per
cent increase in after-tax profits to Dollars 216.4m.
GM Acceptance Corporation, the financial services arm, reported after-tax
profits of Dollars 245m, up from Dollars 205m.
</TEXT>
