   By BRUCE JACQUES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
John Fairfax Holdings, the Australian newspaper group, has foreshadowed a
potential move into electronic and digital technology with a possible
investment of up to ADollars 1bn (Dollars 740m) later this decade, writes
Bruce Jacques in Sydney. Mr Stephen Mulholland, chief executive, yesterday
told a Securities Institute of Australia lunch the company was negotiating a
pay television deal which would involve equity of ADollars 10m-ADollars 12m
and borrowings of a similar amount.
