1bn in the information technology area, either in Australia or overseas,
after 1997 when its debt-to-equity ratio was expected to be below 20 per
cent.
Mr Mulholland reiterated that Fairfax was negotiating a plan to link with a
leading, but unnamed, US database provider. The company was also planning to
launch a Saturday edition of the Australian Financial Review early next
year.
