<HEADLINE>
FT  21 OCT 94 / International Company News: Modest growth for
Colgate-Palmolive
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD TOMKINS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Colgate-Palmolive, the US consumer products group, posted modest growth in
the three months to September with a 6 per cent increase in net income to
Dollars 151m, writes Richard Tomkins. As in the second quarter, the bright
spot was the growth in overseas sales, particularly in emerging markets. The
biggest drag on profits was the continued downturn in North American sales,
attributed to reductions in retail inventories.
Group revenues, boosted by growth in emerging markets, rose by 6 per cent to
Dollars 1.9bn. Operating profits were 13 per cent ahead at Dollars 255.7m,
but net income was hit by a big increase in the interest charge.
Earnings per share, boosted by extensive company share repurchases, rose by
12 per cent to Dollars 1.00.
