<HEADLINE>
FT  21 OCT 94 / International Company News: Earthquake losses continue to
shake Sears, Roebuck results
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LAURIE MORSE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CHICAGO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
January's California earth-quake again shook Sears, Roebuck's bottom line in
the third quarter, with additional catastrophe losses announced by its
Allstate insurance subsidiary in September reducing the US retailer's net
income by Dollars 182.4m.
Allstate yesterday reported its quake-related losses had reached Dollars
845m for the first nine months of the year, with Sears' share of those
losses at Dollars 677.1m.
Income growth at Sears' merchandising division helped offset the insurance
losses, with Sears reporting third-quarter earnings of Dollars 363.5m, or 91
cents a share, down from Dollars 388.4m, or 98 cents, in last year's third
quarter.
Sales for the quarter were up about 3.8 per cent, to Dollars 13.2bn, from
last year's Dollars 12.7bn.
Sears' Merchandise Group recorded third-quarter net income of Dollars 196m,
up from Dollars 159m last year, while sales rose to Dollars 7.7bn from
Dollars 7.3bn last time.
'Our core retailing and insurance businesses continued to post very good
operating performances in the quarter, highlighted by the Mer-chandise
Group's earnings in-crease of about 24 per cent and Allstate's significantly
improv-ed underwriting performance excluding the impact of the earthquake,'
said Mr Edward Brennan, Sears chairman.
'The fundamentals of our Sears and Allstate businesses are very sound,' he
added.
For the first nine months net income was Dollars 769.0m, or Dollars 1.92 a
share, on revenues of Dollars 38.48bn. In the same 1993 period Sears had
income of Dollars 1.83bn, or Dollars 4.73, which included a Dollars 635.1m
gain from Allstate's share offering. Sears' revenues in the period last year
were Dollars 36.17bn.
Allstate, 80.1 per cent owned by Sears, separately reported its
third-quarter income at Dollars 193.9m, or 43 cents, down sharply from
Dollars 325.7m, or 72 cents, last time.
The company said losses from the California earthquake reduced third-quarter
earnings by 51 cents a share. Allstate's third-quarter revenues were Dollars
5.39bn, up from Dollars 5.32bn.
For the nine months Allstate's income was Dollars 320.7m, or 71 cents,
against Dollars 1.04bn, or Dollars 2.42. Sales for the period were Dollars
16.03bn, up from Dollars 15.66bn.
</TEXT>
