<HEADLINE>
FT  21 OCT 94 / International Company News: Kaufhof and Horten propose store
merger
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By Agencies
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Kaufhof Holding, the German retailer, and Horten, Germany's fourth-biggest
department store group, are proposing to merge their retail operations
within the Kaufhof group, a joint statement said yesterday, agencies report.
The proposal reflects Kaufhof's determination to push through
rationalisation in the depressed department store sector. Kaufhof took a
majority stake in Horten this summer and is offering to buy out the 41 per
cent of Horten's shares it does not already own.
Horten shareholders are being offered DM200 a share, which values the
company at about DM1bn (Dollars 666m).
Lex, Page 18
