<HEADLINE>
FT  21 OCT 94 / UK Company News: Suter disposals
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Suter has sold its 12 acre site at Fareham, Hampshire to Legal &amp; General
Assurance Society for Pounds 6.75m cash, subject to a 25 year leaseback to
Suter Environmental.
Suter also announced the disposal of Deritend Engineering for a nominal sum.
DEL, a non-core business, makes printing and die cutting machinery for use
in the box making industry and was acquired as part of the James Wilkes
group in May.
