<HEADLINE>
FT  21 OCT 94 / UK Company News: Yorklyde up 14%
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Yorklyde, the Huddersfield-based clothing manufacturer, reported pre-tax
profits up 14 per cent at Pounds 1.7m for the six months to July 31, against
Pounds 1.49m.
The company said the benefits of its investment programme were now being
felt and the continuing development of the product range had helped maintain
a healthy level of interest.
Turnover was Pounds 9.22m (Pounds 7.87m) a rise of 17 per cent. Earnings per
share were 11.4p (10.2p) and the interim dividend is raised to 2.4p (2.2p).
