<TEXT>
Shares in Azlan Group, a distributor of advanced computer networking
products which came to the market in November at 230p, fell sharply again
yesterday.
The shares, which have fallen from a peak of 281p in June, shed a further
32p yesterday in thin trading to close at 128p.
The company did not issue a statement, but there were market rumours that a
large institutional investor had become disenchanted with high technology
new issues in general and had decided to sell.
The collapse in the group's share price began in June after the company
issued a warning that profits in the first half of the current year would
not match those of last year.
