</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Very sorry I can't hand out your school prizes - I've got to hot-foot it
back to Sofia to be Bulgaria's new foreign minister. Not an excuse often
heard by school heads, but one that Christopher Barnett of Croydon's
Whitgift School had to accept on Monday night when his star turn, Ivan
Stancioff, former Bulgarian ambassador in London, pulled out at the last
minute. However Aglika Markova, the embassy's cultural attache, filled the
slot admirably. She informed pupils that Bulgarian education has come a long
way from the days when teachers were forced to tell their pupils that
aeroplanes and steam engines were invented in Russia in the 16th century.
