<HEADLINE>
FT  21 OCT 94 / People: New board members at Grand Metropolitan
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Peter Job, 53, the much travelled chief executive of Reuters, and Michael
Hepher, 50, the ex-chief executive of Lloyds Abbey Life and current group
managing director of BT, have accepted their first big outside
directorships.
They have been appointed non-executive directors of Grand Metropolitan. They
will serve for a term of three years.
When they take their seats on November 24 they will join a boardroom which
contains British Airways' chairman Sir Colin Marshall, British Gas chairman
Richard Giordano, David Simon, BP chief executive, and Sir John
Harvey-Jones, a former chairman of ICI and star of the BBC TV
'Troubleshooter' series.
When Sir John retires at the end of the year GrandMet will have six
non-executive directors and six executive directors.
</TEXT>
