FT  21 OCT 94 / Technology (Worth Watching): Whiteboards and PCs team up
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By VANESSA HOULDER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A laser scanning system which allows presentations on whiteboards to be
simultaneously displayed on a PC has been introduced in the UK by Microfield
Graphics, an Oregon-based company.
The SoftBoard depends on an infra-red laser system tracking the colour and
movement of a marker with a reflective bar-coded sleeve. The data stream is
sent to a digital signal processor which presents the graphic image on a
computer display.
