FT  21 OCT 94 / BSkyB wins merger appeal
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
British Sky Broadcasting yesterday won an appeal against a judgment in
favour of Philips, the consumer electronics group, arising from the merger
between Sky and BSB.
The Commercial Court had found that there was an implied contract that BSB
should do nothing to impede the market for BSB receivers being manufactured
by Philips.
The Court of Appeal decided there was no such contract.
