<HEADLINE>
FT  21 OCT 94 / Views sought on planned Gas split
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID LASCELLES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Key aspects of the planned split of British Gas into trading and
transportation arms are reviewed in a consultation document by Ofgas, the
industry regulator, published yesterday, David Lascelles writes.
Ofgas is seeking comments on terms which would oblige TransCo, the
transportation and storage arm, to offer the same terms to British Gas and
independent gas suppliers.
The regulator said: 'Short of divestment, full and effective separation
represents the best protection against British Gas' trading businesses
benefiting from being part of the same company as Transco.'
Mr Cedric Brown, British Gas chief executive, said it was a 'tough but
realistic package' but added: 'We recognise the need for effective
separation at home but this must not hinder our ability to compete
successfully in overseas markets.'
