FT  21 OCT 94 / Gatwick Express to dilute adverts
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHARLES BATCHELOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Gatwick Express, the train operating company which runs Gatwick station, is
to tone down its advertising and give greater prominence to the activities
of competing services following an investigation by the rail regulator,
Charles Batchelor writes.
Mr John Swift QC, the regulator, said yesterday that he accepted that
Gatwick Express was taking 'the appropriate management action' to ensure its
staff acted impartially. He will continue to monitor the situation.
The investigation was requested by the franchising director, responsible for
selling rail franchises to the private sector, to establish rules of good
practice before companies moved into the private sector.
