<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The US and Britain formally warned Iraq last night that any further threat
to Kuwait through troop movements beyond the 32nd parallel would be met by
force. The two powers acted, in demarches by their UN ambassadors, in a
follow-up to last weekend's Security Council resolution demanding complete
withdrawal of troops Iraq deployed in setting off the recent crisis.
Diplomats said France was expected to issue a parallel warning but probably
not threaten a specific military res-ponse, since it had not interpreted the
resolution as auth-orising a further use of force. The US and Britain told
Iraq's UN delegate they were ready to 'respond appropriately and decisively'
to any new threat.
