earlier this year by the long-distance telecommunications group AT&amp;T.
The turnround in profitability at Lin was partly accredited to continued
growth in its core cellular business - subscribers were up 200,000 at
974,000 from a year earlier.
Revenues from Lin's television station business, which the company plans to
spin off to shareholders later this year, rose 7 per cent during the quarter
to Dollars 42.3m.
