<HEADLINE>
FT  20 OCT 94 / World Stock Markets: Brazil
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Equities retreated to close 3.1 per cent down in light trade on the Sao
Paulo bourse as investors sold on concern about probable government
restrictions on foreign funds into the country and a possible higher minimum
wage. The Bovespa index fell 1,509 to 47,587.
Brazil's real declined sharply against the dollar in the commercial foreign
exchange yesterday as players rushed to the US currency after the news of
possible restrictions. The real closed 1.3 per cent down at RDollars 0.858
to the dollar after the central bank sold dollars in the market to help the
local unit.
The approval yesterday by a Lower House committee of a proposal to increase
Brazil's minimum wage to RDollars 100 from RDollars 70 as of December also
weighed on prices.
