<HEADLINE>
FT  20 OCT 94 / World Stock Markets: Markets in perspective
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The listing this week in New York and locally of Indosat, the Indonesian
telecommunications company, has given a boost to the Jakarta market, which
has been languishing so far this year a long way behind its regional
competitors.
The global offering of shares in the group, the largest in Asia, raised
about Dollars 1bn. Brokers say this should provide a much needed stimulus to
the equity market and encourage the return of foreign investors. Yesterday
Indosat made a successful debut on the local exchange, initially gaining
nearly 30 per cent on its IPO price of Rp7,000 before falling back on
profit-taking to close at Rp8,475.
One difficulty facing the market's forward progress remains the limit on the
foreign ownership of companies, currently at 49 per cent, which is not, at
least in the short term, to be lifted.
