</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LAURIE MORSE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CHICAGO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Cummins, the Indiana-based diesel engine maker, yesterday said third-quarter
income rose to Dollars 61.9m, or Dollars 1.48 a share, from last year's
Dollars 40.7m, or Dollars 1.11, writes Laurie Morse in Chicago.
Sales for the quarter were a record Dollars 1.2bn, up from Dollars 988.3m in
last year's third quarter.
Strong sales in US medium-duty and heavy-duty truck markets lifted results.
The company said it expected North American heavy-duty truck production to
reach a record 205,000 units in 1994, up 20 per cent over 1993.
