<HEADLINE>
FT  20 OCT 94 / UK Company News: Derwent Valley rises to Pounds 3.8m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
An exceptional profit of Pounds 1.58m from associates enabled Derwent Valley
Holdings, the property group, to hoist pre-tax profits from Pounds 1.12m to
Pounds 3.77m in the first half of 1994.
Net rental income, benefiting from recent acquisitions, grew 45 per cent to
Pounds 4.65m (Pounds 3.22m).
The exceptional credit arose from settlement of the residual liability in
Dorrington Derwent Investments, following the disposal of that company's
investment properties in 1993.
Adjusted earnings per share were 6.46p (4.78p). The interim dividend is
1.58p (adjusted 1.525p) on increased capital.
</TEXT>
