FT  20 OCT 94 / Domestic gas prices 'to fall'
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Domestic consumers should see gas prices fall by between 8 per cent and 12
per cent once the market is fully deregulated, independent gas companies
told MPs yesterday.
At a hearing of the trade and industry committee managers of companies which
hope to enter the gas market once British Gas' monopoly is ended said the
average price cut across the country would be 10 per cent.
